  "description": "Christian monk, priest, hymnographer and apologist (675/6-749)",
  "bio": "大馬士革的聖若望（阿拉伯語：يوحنا الدمشقي，拉丁化：Yuḥannā Al Demashqi；希臘語：Ιωάννης Δαμασκήνος，拉丁化：Iôannês Damaskênos；拉丁語：Iohannes Damascenus，約676年—749年12月4日），天主教譯為聖若望·達瑪森（St. John Damascene），生於大馬士革的基督宗教神學家、詩人及聖樂家。",
  "bio_source": "zhwiki",
  "description_en": "Christian monk, priest, hymnographer and apologist (675/6-749)",
  "bio_en": "John of Damascus or John Damascene, born Yūḥana ibn Manṣūr ibn Sarjūn, was a Christian monk, priest, hymnographer, and apologist. He was born and raised in Damascus c. AD 675 or AD 676; the precise date and place of his death is not known, though tradition places it at his monastery, Mar Saba, near Jerusalem, on 4 December AD 749. A polymath whose fields of interest and contribution included law, theology, philosophy, and music, he was given the by-name of Chrysorroas (Χρυσορρόας, literally \"streaming with gold\", i.e. \"the golden speaker\").",
  "bio_en_source": "enwiki"
}